.nfs*

# Exception: this package ships test fixtures that are deliberately named like
# OS junk, so the static server's junk-filter tests have real files on disk.
# Re-include the whole fixture tree so the rules above never drop them. The
# directory is negated explicitly because git will not descend into an excluded
# directory (.AppleDouble) to re-include a file inside it.
!/unirend-php/tests/fixtures/junk-assets/**/
!/unirend-php/tests/fixtures/junk-assets/**

# Exception: these two directories are named "build" but are committed source,
# not build output. One is a checked-in sample of what the PHP mirror serves,
# the other is the fixture tree its tests read. The broad `build/` rule above
# matches both, and they only survived because git tracks them already, which
# hid the mismatch: every rules-based tool saw them as generated. Negated
# directory-first for the same reason as the block above.
!/unirend-php/demo/build/
!/unirend-php/demo/build/**
!/unirend-php/tests/fixtures/build/
!/unirend-php/tests/fixtures/build/**

